<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12186n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12186n">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12186n"> 186(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> catechumenate</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It was the idea of the old Christian <mark>Catechumenate</mark> that was followed by St. Reinilda, and it is this same idea that has been realized anew in the St. Reinilda Stichting. The Catechumenate existed in the Church as long as there were pagans, and especially pagan children, to be converted. <small> G. Van Gestel, &ldquo;The St. Reinilda Congregation of Holland&rdquo; <a name="STRC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STRC"><cite title="source">Studies</cite></a> (March 1924) 131</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
